Hey Arthur,

I am glad to see that you still remember my last problem. :\)

Well, I did fresh installation of 18.04. And also did all the setup installation on the Native Installation page.

I did the libgoogle-glog-dev installation. It removes the earlier error. But found 2 below error logs.

‌

`[FATAL] [1567337888.012773662, 12.571000000]: Failed to create the dwa_local_planner/DWAPlannerROS planner, are you sure it is properly registered and that the containing library is built? Exception: According to the loaded plugin descriptions the class dwa_local_planner/DWAPlannerROS with base class type nav_core::BaseLocalPlanner does not exist. Declared types are  base_local_planner/TrajectoryPlannerROS`  
`[alpha/move_base-13] process has died [pid 16814, exit code 1, cmd /opt/ros/melodic/lib/move_base/move_base map:=projected_map __name:=move_base __log:=/home/baila/.ros/log/38eaf2fe-c9b8-11e9-9100-68a3c4a1e180/alpha-move_base-13.log].`  
`log file: /home/baila/.ros/log/38eaf2fe-c9b8-11e9-9100-68a3c4a1e180/alpha-move_base-13*.log`

‌

and

‌

`[ERROR] [1567338070.684413, 37.394000]: bad callback: <bound method Detector.image_cb of <main.Detector instance at 0x7fe7a0769f38>>`  
`Traceback (most recent call last):`  
`File "/opt/ros/melodic/lib/python2.7/dist-packages/rospy/topics.py", line 750, in _invoke_callback`  
`cb(msg)`  
`File "/home/baila/subt_hello_world/catkin_build_ws/src/tensorflow_object_detector/scripts/detect_ros.py", line 99, in image_cb`  
`(boxes, scores, classes, num_detections) = self.sess.run([boxes, scores, classes, num_detections],`

any clue?
